	$dqs[]="To make strong ale: Thames-Water taken up about Greenwich at Low-water, when it is free from all brackishness of the sea, and has in it all the Fat and Sullage from this Great City of London, makes very Strong Drink. It will itself ferment wonderfully and after its due purgations and three times stink it will be so strong that several Sea Commanders have told me that it has often fuddled their Murriners. -- Brewer's Guide, London, 1702";
