	$dqs[]="Drinking wine before beer is a no-no, dear. Topping beer off with wine - that's fine! -- German proverb";
	$dqs[]="Ale is made of malte and water; and they the whiche do put any other thynge to ale than is rehersed, except yest, barme or godesgood, doth sophysticat theyr ale. -- Andrew Boorde's 1542 (A Compendious Regyment or a Dyetary of Helth)'";
	$dqs[]="It is my design to die in the brewhouse, let ale be placed to my mouth when I am expiring so that when the choir of angels come they may say: 'Be God propitious to this drinker.' -- St. Columbanus";
	$dqs[]="A glass of bitter or pale ale, taken with the principal meal of the day, does more good and less harm than any medicine the physician can prescibe. -- Dr. S. Carpenter, England, 1750";
	$dqs[]="God bless the Woman who gives birth to a brewer. -- Anonymous";
	$dqs[]="I have never been into wine. I'm a beer man. What I like about beer is you basically just drink it and order more. You don't sniff at it, or hold it up to the light and slosh it around, or drone on and on about it, the way people do with wine. Your beer drinker tends to be a straightforward, decent, friendly, down-to-earth person, whereas your serious wine fancier tends to be an insufferable snot. -- Dave Barry";
	$dqs[]="That's right, lovers of 'music-you-can't-dance-to' have taken a shine to beer. As one particularly insensitive rooter remarked, 'There's nothing like laying your head back on the satin head rest, almost tapping your foot, and knocking down a couple of brews.' -- Lynne O'Connor (on the Austin, Texas Symphony's First Annual Beer Tasting and Benefit in Southwest Brewing News)";
	$dqs[]="History flows forward in rivers of beer. -- Anonymous";
	$dqs[]="Got Beer? -- Walter Breidenstein";
	$dqs[]="In Belgium, the magistrate has the dignity of a prince, but by Bacchus, it is true that the brewer is king. -- Emile Verhaeren, Flemish writer, 1855-1916";
	$dqs[]="I am the first man south of the Mason-Dixon line to brew a drinkable home-brew. -- H.L. Mencken (Heathen Days)";
	$dqs[]="I've always believed that paradise will have my favorite beer on tap. -- Rudyard Wheatley";
	$dqs[]="You can never buy beer... you just rent it. -- Archie Bunker";
	$dqs[]="The man who called it 'near beer' was a bad judge of distance. -- Philander Johnson/Luke McLuke, Cincinnati Enquirer";
	$dqs[]="Fill with mingled cream and amber, I will drain that glass again. Such hilarious visions clamber through the chambers of my brain. Quaintest thoughts --queerest fancies, come to life and fade away. What care I how time advances? I am drinking ale today. -- Edgar Allan Poe";
	$dqs[]="I should like a great lake of ale, for the King of Kings. I should like the family of heaven to be drinking it through time eternal. -- St. Brigid";
	$dqs[]="It's a sign of the times. Beer is no longer the special reserve of the bowling league or the dart league. Neither is it the province of bourgeois country music lovers, or divan-impaled aficionados of the goal-line stand. It's true. Beer has lost it's elitist status; it's proletarianized. Beer has descended to the symphony. -- Lynne O'Connor (on the Austin, Texas Symphony's First Annual Beer Tasting and Benefit in Southwest Brewing News)";
	$dqs[]="There is more to life than beer alone, but beer makes those other things even better. -- Stephen Morris (The Great Beer Trek)";
	$dqs[]="There are those descended from an unawakened race of men who did not receive and do not revere the yeast. These sometimes attempt to brew-rather, merely manipulate ingredients-and swill the festered residues. But not to them is revealed the simplicity of art, either of beer or of poetry. Not for them is the beatitude of the true Malt; such people are cultural dropouts. -- John F Adams";
	$dqs[]="It was estimated that some five thousand people were trampled to death in the stampede for free beer at the coronation of Czar Nicholas II in Moscow in May 1896. -- Guinness Book Of World Records";
	$dqs[]="Friends don't let friends drink Lite Beer. -- Anonymous";
	$dqs[]="Praise not the day until evening has come; a woman until she is burnt; a sword until it is tried; a maiden until she is married; ice until it has been crossed; beer until it has been drunk. -- Viking Proverb";
	$dqs[]="Listening to someone who brews his own beer is like listening to a religious fanatic talk about the day he saw the light. -- Ross Murray, Montreal Gazette";
	$dqs[]="I never met a free beer I didn't like. -- Brent Runyon";
	$dqs[]="Wine is on every lip: beer in every stomach. Those same writers who prate about priceless wines, drink beer. -- Anonymous, 1934";
	$dqs[]="Gimme a pigfoot and a bottle of beer. -- Bessie Smith (Song written by Wesley Sox Wilson, 1933)";
	$dqs[]="Water is good for only two things: floating ships and making beer. -- Anonymous";
	$dqs[]="Prohibition has made our president a dictator, executing an unpopular law by force of arms. It has made our congressmen cowards and hypocrites, passing more, and more oppressive laws, while themselves carrying whisky flasks in their hip pockets. Prohibition has divided our people into factions almost as bitterly hostile to each other as the factions that existed before the Civil War. -- William Randolph Hearst, 1932";
	$dqs[]="Matthew Vassar's gen'rous heart put a brain in every lass. He made his beer and college here for the good of the Freshman class. -- Quote about the founder of Vassar College, who had beeen a brewer in Poughkeepsie, NY";
	$dqs[]="I feel wonderful, drinking beer in a blissful mood, with joy in my heart and a happy liver. -- Sumerian inscription, 3000 B.C.";
	$dqs[]="Most people hate the taste of beer to begin with. It is, however, a prejudice that many people have been able to overcome. -- Winston Churchill";
	$dqs[]="Hey, bartender, a thousand pints of light! -- Second City Players";
	$dqs[]="They didn't trademark everything back then. Now someone farts and they put a TM after it. Even Miller Lite says 'A Fine Pilsener Beer' on the label. It is a crime. -- Michael Jackson";
	$dqs[]="Payday came and with it beer. -- Kipling";
	$dqs[]="Give me a woman who loves beer and I will conquer the world. -- Kaiser Wilhelm";
	$dqs[]="If God had intended us to drink beer, he would have given us stomachs. -- David Daye";
	$dqs[]="Beer by Christmas would be the most welcome news the American people could have since the depression began. -- William Randolph Hearst, November 10, 1932";
	$dqs[]="Beer that is not drunk has missed its vocation. -- Meyer Breslau";
	$dqs[]="I would give all my fame for a pot of ale and safety. -- William Shakespeare (King Henry V)";
	$dqs[]="It's a fair wind that blew man to the ale. -- Washington Irving";
	$dqs[]="If the headache would only precede the intoxication, alcoholism would be a virtue. -- Samuel Butler";
	$dqs[]="Good ale will make a cat speak. -- Old English proverb";
	$dqs[]="The immense importance of a pint of ale to a common person should never be overlooked. -- Canon of St. Paul's Cathedral";
	$dqs[]="I have received delegations of working men who, apparently speaking with the utmost sincerity, have declared that they would regard it as a genuine hardship to be deprived of their beer. -- Woodrow Wilson";
	$dqs[]="An' damn the eyes, whoever tries, to rob a poor man of his beer. -- British Music Hall Song, 1830";
	$dqs[]="Beer has food value, but food has no beer value. -- Anonymous";
	$dqs[]="What's made Milwaukee famous, made a loser out of me. -- Jerry Lee Lewis";
	$dqs[]="Lynne was 'underwhelmed: it's soapy and looks like frog spawn.' -- Lynne Pearce, discussing Erdinger Weiss beer (What's Brewing, June, 1994)";
	$dqs[]="Dost thou think, because thou art virtuous, there shall be no more cakes and ale? -- William Shakespheare (Twelfth Night)";
	$dqs[]="Real ale fans are just like train-spotters, only drunk. -- Christopher Howse";
	$dqs[]="Why, we'll smoke and drink our beer. For I like a drop of good beer, I does. I'ze fond of good beer, I is. Let gentlemen fine sit down to their wine. But we'll all of us here stick to our beer. -- Old Somersetshire English song";
	$dqs[]="They can have my beer when they pry it out of my cold, dead hand. -- Ben Schwalb";
	$dqs[]="He that buys land buys many stones. He that buys flesh buys many bones. He that buys eggs buys many shells. He that buys good ale buys nothing else. -- John Ray (1627 - 1705)";
	$dqs[]="People, in a sense, wear their beer as much as they drink their beer. -- Ira Matathia, advertising executive, Toronto Star, May 10, 1991";
	$dqs[]="You can't be a real country unless you have a beer and an airline - it helps if you have some kind of a football team, or some nuclear weapons, but at the very least you need a beer. -- Frank Zappa";
	$dqs[]="That Osiris founded there the dynasty of the Beer Kings. -- Peluseum, Ancient Egypt";
	$dqs[]="They, the Vikings, drink beer to insensibility day and night. It often happens that one of them dies with his cup in his hand. -- Ian Fadhlan, 922 A.D.";
	$dqs[]="The hardest part about making beer is siphoning it into bottles. This is tricky, because what can happen is the phone rings and you get involved in a lengthy conversation during which your 4 year-old son gets hold of the hose and spews premature beer, called wort, all over the kitchen and himself, and you become the target of an investigation by child welfare authorities because yours is the only child who comes to preschool smelling like a fraternity carpet. -- Dave Barry";
	$dqs[]="I drank only water; the other workmen, near 50 in number, were great guzzlers of beer. We had an alehouse boy who attended always in the house to supply the workmen. My companion at the press, drank every day a pint before breakfast, a pint at breakfast with his bread and cheese; a pint in the afternoon about six o'clock, and another when he'd done his day's work...but it was necessary, he suppos'd, to drink strong beer that he might be strong to labor. Those who continu'd sotting with beer all day, were often, by not paying out of credit at the alehouse, and us'd to make interest with me to get beer, their light, as they phras'd it, being out. -- Benjamin Franklin (The Autobiography)";
	$dqs[]="No personage in Blegic tradition has been more recommended than King Gambrinus. To this day, the students annually choose one of their number who drinks the most beer to be their 'Beer King', whom they induct into a chair placed under a picture of Gambrinus, and who henceforth becomes the authority in all matters relating in the consumption of beer. -- Coremans, Dorchester, 1884";
	$dqs[]="The Oktoberfest is a big beer party, and this is big beer culture. -- Georg Schneider Vof German Privatbrauerei G. Schneider & Sohn while visiting the Great American Beer Festival";
	$dqs[]="In some countries, when a boy reaches a certain age it is customary for his father to take him to a bordello so as to ensure his proper initiation into one of life's greatest pleasures. In England, the equivalent custom is for the father to take his son on his first visit to a pub and to supervise his initiation into the ritual of beer-drinking in a proper social environment. -- Terry Foster (Pale Ale)";
	$dqs[]="The selling of bad beer is a crime against Christian love. -- 13th Century Law from the City of Augsburg";
	$dqs[]="Ale sellers should not be tale tellers. -- Old Scottish proverb";
	$dqs[]="Life alas, is very drear. Up with the glass, down with the beer! -- Louis Untermeyer";
	$dqs[]="Cerevisia malorum. divina medicina (A little bit of beer is divine medicine.) -- Paracelsus - 16th century physician";
	$i = rand ( 0 , count($dqs) );
	return $dqs[$i];
}



